name: T.O.T.S.
overview: A heartfelt animated comedy series for preschoolers exploring the hilarious adventures of best friends Pip and Freddy, a tenacious penguin and a kind-hearted flamingo, who are the only non-stork delivery birds in-training at Tiny Ones Transport Service (T.O.T.S.).

episodes.name: You've Gotta Be Kitten Me
episodes.overview: On Pip and Freddy's first day as Junior Fliers, they deliver a kitten who mistakes them for her parents.

episodes.name: Whale, Hello There
episodes.overview: When there is a two-ton baby whale who needs delivering, the fliers compete for the task.

episodes.name: Panda Excess
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy must deliver a baby panda so cute, that it makes it hard to say goodbye.

episodes.name: A Stinky Situation
episodes.overview: The Junior Fliers have trouble delivering a baby skunk due to its overwhelming smell.

episodes.name: Cheetah Chase
episodes.overview: When a cheetah is accidentally set loose, Pip and Freddy must play a game of tag to catch it.

episodes.name: Training Daze
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy find themselves leading a group of storks on a class trip.

episodes.name: Nursery Schooling
episodes.overview: After K.C. gets sick, Pip and Freddy watch the babies in the Nursery for her.

episodes.name: Bunny Bunanza
episodes.overview: When delivery batches of bunnies get mixed up, the Junior Fliers must figure out which bunny is which.

episodes.name: The Purrfect Little Helper
episodes.overview: When Pip and Freddy have to deliver a kitten, they think it's a mistake since there are no cats at T.O.T.S.

episodes.name: The Colorful Chameleon
episodes.overview: The Junior Fliers must deliver a baby chameleon that keeps disappearing.

episodes.name: Stripe Out
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy try to find out what kind of mysterious striped animal they are delivering.

episodes.name: A Splashy Delivery
episodes.overview: The Junior Fliers accidentally spring a leak in a delivery crate containing a baby octopus.

episodes.name: Night Flight
episodes.overview: Pip hopes to speed through the next delivery but is tasked with delivering a baby sloth.

episodes.name: Slippery When Wet
episodes.overview: Freddy must face his fear of the dark when he and Pip are assigned a nighttime delivery.

episodes.name: Hiccup Hazard
episodes.overview: When Pip's hiccups threaten a delivery, he asks Freddy to scare them out of him.

episodes.name: The Great Robot Race
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy attempt to prove that delivery birds are better than a stork drone.

episodes.name: Back to Cool
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy deliver a baby Penguin to Pip's hometown.

episodes.name: Baby Breakdown
episodes.overview: When Pip and Freddy break the conveyor belt at T.O.T.S. they are determined to fix it on their own.

episodes.name: Lost Lovey
episodes.overview: Mia loses lovey, so Pip and Freddy go on a wild chase to find it.

episodes.name: Diggity Dog
episodes.overview: The Fliers' delivery is in jeopardy when their puppy student becomes the master at digging.

episodes.name: Temple of the Tiger
episodes.overview: Freddy and Pip try their hardest to keep a baby tiger prince clean.

episodes.name: The Gift-Mazing Birthday
episodes.overview: When a baby arrives on its birthday, Freddy tries to find the perfect birthday present.

episodes.name: Like Cats and Dogs
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy must teach squabbling kitten and puppy siblings to share.

episodes.name: The Bouncy Bouncy Baby
episodes.overview: Pip gets locked inside a crate with a baby kangaroo.

episodes.name: For Lion Out Loud
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy teach a lion cub the difference between his indoor and outdoor roar.

episodes.name: Porcupine Panic
episodes.overview: When a porcupine fears the delivery tube, K.C. and the Fliers help him beat his fear.

episodes.name: The Fearful Flier
episodes.overview: Bodhi faces his fear to earn his final stamp towards becoming a Super Flier.

episodes.name: Lend Me Your Paw
episodes.overview: After Mia gets a thorn stuck in her paw, she worries it will hurt when K.C. tries to take it out.

episodes.name: Monkeying Around and Around
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy deliver a monkey that loves to play pretend so much, it gets in the way of his delivery.

episodes.name: Koala Kuisine
episodes.overview: K.C. makes something tasty for a baby hippo that refuses to eat its food.

episodes.name: Bringing Back Baby

episodes.name: A Penguin in the Desert
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy brave the desert heat to deliver a camel.

episodes.name: Out Foxed
episodes.overview: Freddy’s status as the best hide-and-seeker is challenged after he and Pip lose a baby fox.

episodes.name: Elephant in the Room
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy help K.C. earn her first Golden Feather on Cleaning Day.

episodes.name: Santa Baby
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy teach a magical baby reindeer the joy of Christmas giving.

episodes.name: Shear Madness
episodes.overview: When Pip and Freddy accidentally shave a baby sheep’s wool, they struggle to fix it before delivering it to its parents.

episodes.name: The Fly-Along
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy must impress Captain Beakman when she joins them for a ride-a-long delivery.

episodes.name: Rock-A-Bye Birdie
episodes.overview: When Mimi the mockingbird sings K.C.'s lullaby, she puts everyone at T.O.T.S. to sleep.

episodes.name: The Valentine Spirit
episodes.overview: Freddy and Pip rush to deliver Valentines to the babies they’ve delivered to make it back in time for the Valentine’s Day Party.

episodes.name: Shell Games
episodes.overview: Freddy, Pip and K.C. try to get a shy turtle out of her shell.

episodes.name: The Fastest Flier
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy teach Ava that there is more to a delivery than speed.

episodes.name: Best Friends Wherever
episodes.overview: When Mia can't say goodbye to her friend, Chloe, the Junior Fliers show her that they can keep in touch!

episodes.name: The Ultimate Easter Egg Hunt
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy’s next delivery gets mixed up with the other eggs for the Annual Easter Egg Hunt.

episodes.name: A Chewy Challenge
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy must deliver a baby beaver, who is chewing and gnawing on everything in sight.

episodes.name: Night at the Nursery
episodes.overview: The Junior Fliers help Oscar, an otter pup, who has trouble sleeping.

episodes.name: Seas The Day
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy make their first underwater delivery. But Freddy, however, isn't a good swimmer.

episodes.name: Daddy Delivery
episodes.overview: While Pip and Freddy make a delivery on Father's Day, a baby Hedgehog gets stuck atop a hill and is too afraid to come down.

episodes.name: Junior Flier JP
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy help JP become a Super Duper Flier again after he gets demoted for failing to take a test.

episodes.name: Bringing This Family Home
episodes.overview: Freddy and Pip help fly KC's family home to meet their baby cousin.

episodes.name: Flight of the Penguin
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy try to deliver two babies at once.

episodes.name: Puppy Problems
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy deliver a puppy that seems like a perfect angel, but turns out to be a mischievous rascal.

episodes.name: The Mighty Little Dragon
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy pretend to be knights while delivering a Komodo dragon.

episodes.name: Mid-Air Care
episodes.overview: KC joins Pip and Freddy for T.O.T.S.' first-ever mid-air baby preparation.

episodes.name: The Itsy Bitsy Baby
episodes.overview: While delivering Calvin, a baby caterpillar, Pip and Freddy witness the greatest magic show of all.

episodes.name: The Big Little Baby
episodes.overview: Mr. Woodbird's big-o-nator is accidentally used on a baby gorilla.

episodes.overview: Kid storks Jed, Red, and Zed take on Pip and Freddy's latest delivery, which is a baby moose named Matilda.

episodes.name: Good Vibrations
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy become helicopter parents towards their latest delivery, a baby mole named Molly.

episodes.name: Mission to the Moon
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy deliver Willa, a female baby wolf, who dreams of seeing the moon.

episodes.name: Say Cheese
episodes.overview: It's Picture Day at T.O.T.S., and Pip and Freddy attempt to get the ever-mischievous puppy, Lucky, ready for the event.

episodes.name: The Ring Bear
episodes.overview: Mia requires help when she misplaces her aunt Cora's wedding ring on her wedding day.

episodes.name: Bull of Energy
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy watch over an energetic baby bull named Bucky, and try to keep him out of trouble until his mom returns home.

episodes.name: Under One Roof
episodes.overview: After a baby giraffe named Gio is found to be too big for his forever home, Pip and Freddy try to make his whole family a new one they can all fit in.

episodes.name: A Spooky Delivery
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy try to help JP get into the Halloween spirit.

episodes.name: Mommy's Special Day
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy help Mia make Captain Beakman the most biggest and most special Mother's Day present ever.

episodes.name: All Aboard Babies
episodes.overview: When Lucky takes the baby train for a joyride, the Flyers must stop it.

episodes.name: Far Far From Home
episodes.overview: On the duo's first overnight delivery, Freddy worries they won't finish in time for him to sleep, and he struggles to stay awake.

episodes.name: Toy Trouble
episodes.overview: When Mia has trouble giving away her old toys, Pip and Freddy try to teach her the joys of donating.

episodes.name: TOTSGIVING
episodes.overview: After Lucky nearly ruins TOTSGIVING, Pip, Freddy, and KC set out to save the holiday.

episodes.name: Woodbird's Wish
episodes.overview: Mr. Woodbird always dreamed of making a baby delivery, so Pip and Freddy are here to help.

episodes.name: The Magical Baby
episodes.overview: Freddy believes baby narwhal Nathan is magical.

episodes.name: Loveys on the Loose
episodes.overview: Professor Peacock returns with a new invention, called Lovey-Bots, which unintentionally wreak havoc and threaten the deliveries of a monkey, zebra, and lion, as well as Mr. Woodbird's job.

episodes.name: Hug-A-Pip
episodes.overview: Lucy the Snow Leopard becomes attached to Pip after losing her lovey.

episodes.name: Out of Control Tower
episodes.overview: Paulie’s glasses break, so Pip, Freddy, and Mia take over his Control Tower duties.

episodes.name: The Smiley-est Shark
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy help a baby shark named Stanley make friends, despite his smile scaring the other babies.

episodes.name: The Super Duper Brother
episodes.overview: JP's mail carrying brother PJ visits the facility, and he tries to prove he's better than him at something, following a delivery.

episodes.name: Surfin' Birds
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy participate in a surfing competition, while delivering Sandy, the baby sea turtle.

episodes.name: Grandpa's Great Adventure
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy team up with legendary flier, Grandpa Hank Featherbeak, while delivering a baby stork named Spencer.

episodes.name: Sled Pup
episodes.overview: With Freddy unable to fly, baby husky Hazel, pulls him and Pip sled-style to her delivery, but she keeps getting distracted, helping other babies.

episodes.name: Baby Boogie
episodes.overview: On K.C.'s birthday, the T.O.T.S. crew host a talent show starring babies, including a platypus named Penelope, who has a special way of dancing.

episodes.name: Swimming with Seals

episodes.overview: In order to deliver a baby meerkat named Maya, a treasure hunt ensues!

episodes.name: Up Up and Oh No
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy accidentally let a baby orangutan named Oliver escape from his crate, and must climb after him.

episodes.name: Pajama Party
episodes.overview: When Mia and Lucky won't stop fighting with each other, Pip, Freddy, and K.C. have a pajama party to try and have them get along.

episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy deliver six baby bunnies to a family named the Hareingtons, but they have to babysit them as the parents construct a new nursery, because they only planned for one.

episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy lead JP and Lucky on an adventure to find Lucky's lost bedtime book titled "The Playful Little Puppy".

episodes.name: Thunder and Frightening
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy go on a stormy delivery to deliver a drum-loving baby ostrich named Orville.

episodes.name: Early Birds
episodes.overview: When a baby rooster won’t stop waking everyone up, Pip and Freddy teach him when it's time to be quiet.

episodes.name: Prank You Very Much
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy plan an April Fool's prank for Captain Beakman with their friends and Lucky, but it proves challenging due to her personal experiences.

episodes.name: Zebra Zebra
episodes.overview: Freddy realizes that twin zebra sisters, Zola and Zora, are unique in their own special ways. Song: "Perfect Pair

episodes.name: Snow Place Like Home
episodes.overview: When Peggy and her family come to stay at T.O.T.S., Pip and Freddy try to make them feel right at home!

episodes.name: Team Cutie Patooties
episodes.overview: When Freddy selects only babies to be on their team for the big T.O.T.S. ball game, Pip questions his decision.

episodes.name: The Adorable Artist
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy encourage a baby python named Pollock to express himself through art.

episodes.name: Home Tree Home
episodes.overview: Mia discovers a tiny tree sapling and insists on finding it a perfect home like other TOTS babies!

episodes.name: Copy Cat
episodes.overview: A game of 'Follow the Leader' with a bobcat named Bobbi, gets out of hand thanks to Lucky.

episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy aid a nervous Mia on her first day of school.

episodes.overview: When Tiberius accidentally disturbs his new sister, Tabitha, he must embrace his big brother expertise.

episodes.name: Super Baby
episodes.overview: A baby crab named Cody, loses his beloved security blankie to a baby dolphin named Darcy, who wants to wear it as a cape and pretend she's a superhero.

episodes.name: Missing Mia
episodes.overview: When Mia heads to school for the day, Lucky feels confused and left out.

episodes.name: Wilburt Woodbird
episodes.overview: Mr. Woodbird can't wait to teach his nephew, Wilburt, how to be a builder.

episodes.name: A Nutty Delivery
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy help a young chipmunk named Chico get over his fear of change when his family is moving.

episodes.name: The Protective Papa

episodes.overview: Freddy can’t wait to show baby flamingo, Fiona, all the warm-weather games he loves.

episodes.name: The Brightest Baby
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy help a baby firefly named Frankie learn to shine her light.

episodes.name: Manatee Out of Water

episodes.name: Trunklebee's Day Off

episodes.name: Teeny Tiny Tot
episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy help a small mouse do big things.

episodes.name: Ava and the Egg
episodes.overview: Ava makes a mistake with her delivery.

episodes.overview: Wilburt learns how to think outside the book when he has trouble keeping a baby warthog named Wesley clean.

episodes.name: Mia First

episodes.name: The Great Fredamingo
episodes.overview: Freddy mistakenly thinks he turned Pip into a penguin lovey with his latest magic trick.

episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy struggle to deliver a pony who won’t stop seeking attention.

episodes.overview: Freddy wishes for his birthday to be every day so Mia tries to make his wish come true.

episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy give a skittish armadillo pup a big cowboy hat to help him be brave.

episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy enlist Mr. Woodbird's robot to do all their chores for them and trouble ensues.

episodes.overview: Pip and Freddy discover their latest delivery is not an average, every-day squirrel.

episodes.overview: The team needs to resist Luna's puppy dog eyes if they’re going to deliver her on time.

episodes.overview: When JP and Freddy get stuck together, they must work together to make a delivery.

episodes.overview: When Pip and Freddy go on an underwater delivery they struggle to adjust.

episodes.name: Family-versary
